<br>
A great place to read about this is Corinthians beginning in Chapter 5 (if you have access to a bible you can read this yourself, read through chapter 7).  This section is written by Paul, whom many probably know was a murderer.  He became a Christian and was forgiven his sins.  It is written to the Corinthians, who are believers and have been saved, but they are leading horridly immoral lives.  Paul tells them that though lawful to him, not all things are profitable.  He also tells them not to judge those outside of the faith, but we can judge those within the faith i.e. if someone is an immoral Christian and will not repent, and will not give up that which is immoral, he can be removed from the fellowship of the church. <br>
<br>
